<TEXT>
the fbi said monday it was warning 
churches nationwide to be on the alert for mail bombs 
the warnings stemmed from concerns about similarities between 
two bombs that exploded earlier this year in virginia and texas 
said ron wolfe fbi spokesman here 
the bombs that exploded in a houston church in january and at 
the christian broadcasting network headquarters in virginia last 
month were wrapped similarly and were the same size wolfe said 
were not absolutely positive theyre connected he added 
at a news conference april 29 in north carolina officials said 
both exploding packages bore return addresses in bladen county nc 
richard metz senior postal inspector for north carolina and 
south carolina declined to reveal the exact addresses but said 
they were in the fayetteville area 
the fbi is warning churches to watch for brownpaper wrapped 
packages that measure about 6 inches long 4 inches wide and 3 
inches deep and bear 15 25cent stamps 
wolfe said the fbi telephoned 30 to 40 religious leaders in 
arkansas alone last week every denomination we could think of 
</TEXT>
