sylvester stallone who subdued boxers and 
guerrillas in his rocky and rambo roles got the scare of 
his life when he was mobbed by fans in italy his spokesman says 
he appreciates the respect and love they give to him but they 
should be more careful paul bloch said in a telephone interview 
monday from milan a lot of people could have been injured 
bloch said the incident happened as stallone was leaving a milan 
theater where he had just received a tv networks award as the 
worlds most popular actor 
a crowd of 4000 to 6000 rushed stallones limo and pounded on 
the windows and body and tried to climb on top to get to stallone 
bloch said 
they were chanting rocky rocky rocky they meant well 
but it was really really scary bloch said 
stallones limo finally escaped but was pursued by cars of 
teenage fans forcing him to return to his hotel instead of 
meeting friends for dinner 
he said it was the scariest experience hes ever had before in 
a crowd the spokesman said 
the actors next stop is the cannes film festival in france 
then he will head to philadelphia for a final week of shooting on 
rocky v due for release in november bloch said 
