rep tom mcmillen a former pro basketball 
player thinks congress should get involved in regulating money in 
college sports 
i think our national legislature has the right to be involved 
in looking at the imbalance between academics and athletics the 
maryland democrat told a national press club forum monday 
colleges and even high schools are neglecting their duty to 
provide athletes with a solid education said mcmillen a former 
rhodes scholar who played in the nba 
a bill he introduced last week would encourage high schools to 
require students in extracurricular activities to maintain a c 
average and reward schools with a 10 percent bonus in federal 
money if they stick to the standard 
but mcmillen stressed that problems at high schools reflect 
unbalanced college priorities especially in moneymaking sports 
such as football and basketball 
