two moderate earthquakes shook central 
iran demolishing a school and a number of houses in the village of 
islamabad and surrounding areas tehran radio reported today 
the broadcast monitored in nicosia did not say whether there 
were any casualties 
the stronger quake registered 48 on the richter scale of ground 
motion the radio said the temblors shook the southern township of 
semiran in central isfahan province once at dawn and again at dusk 
monday 
the radio said southern villages have been shaken by earthquakes 
57 times in the past month 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage in a populated area and one of 5 can cause considerable 
damage 
