a shiite moslem leader said today he 
believes no more western hostages will be freed until the israelis 
and their lebanese militia allies release some 400 lebanese shiite 
and palestinian captives 
hussein musawi leader of the fundamentalist islamic amal 
faction also voiced fears that one of the western hostages in 
lebanon could be killed if four missing iranians are found to have 
been slain by christian militiamen 
musawis remarks were seen as an effort to pressure washington 
to make a conciliatory gesture toward iran and the hostagetakers 
following last months release of two american captives 
iran and its lebanese shiite allies have asked the united states 
to help determine the fate of the four missing iranians who were 
seized eight years ago and pressure israel and its militia allies 
in south lebanon to release their prisoners 
if the kidnappers mind is sound and their religion is sound 
they will not free any more hostages said musawi the reputed 
mentor of some of the hostage takers and i think they wont 
if the americans want to solve the hostage issue they should 
solve the problem of the moslems and the oppressed held by israel 
and its surrogates he added 
but musawi warned that if the four iranians were found to have 
