<TEXT>
the fire that broke out early tuesday aboard 
the guidedmissile destroyer uss conyngham off north carolina 
killing one crew member and injuring at least nine others was the 
first serious navy accident since a sixweek string last fall 
those accidents which caused 14 fatalities prompted the navy 
to review safety procedures in november 
here is a rundown of recent serious navy accidents 
oct 11 1989 an officer aboard the helicopter carrier uss iwo 
jima was killed and a crewman was injured when they were struck by 
shrapnel from a shell fired from a nearby cargo ship during an 
exercise in the atlantic ocean 
oct 11 a sailor was lost overboard from the frigate uss 
downes 300 miles off tokyo 
oct 29 a jet fighter pilot making his first carrier landing 
crashed on the deck of the training aircraft carrier uss lexington 
in the gulf of mexico killing himself and four others 
oct 30 the pilot of an fa18 attack jet accidentally dropped 
a 500pound bomb on the cruiser uss reaves in the indian ocean 
slightly injuring five sailors 
oct 30 a sailor from the aircraft carrier uss carl vinson was 
lost overboard in the pacific ocean 620 miles from wake island 
nov 1 three sailors and 4 million worth of aircraft missiles 
were swept overboard from the carrier uss eisenhower off north 
carolina two sailors were rescued and one was declared dead 
nov 1 nine sailors were injured in a boiler fire aboard the 
uss monongahela 500 miles west of gibraltar 
nov 9 a navy reserve pilot flying an a7e attack jet crashed 
into an apartment complex in smyrna ga killing two civilians 
the pilot and one other person were wounded 
nov 11 one man was killed when the destroyer uss kincaid 
collided with a freighter off the coast of malaysia 
nov 14 an f14 fighter crashed into the gulf of mexico 60 
miles northwest of key west fla the twoman crew was not 
seriously injured 
nov 14 a fire aboard the amphibious assault ship uss inchon 
at norfolk va injured 31 people eight of them civilians 
nov 14 a technician at the naval surface weapons testing 
center in white oak md was slightly injured in a small lab 
explosion 
nov 22 two marines were killed in a crash during exercises 
off the iwo jima in the western mediterranean sea 
