you can give us again a heightened sense of the classical 
values of the western spirit a new realization that democracy 
is not just a ballot box it is a wise mature and exacting state 
of mind the heir to the british throne stressed 
from leader to laborer east europeans are basking in this new 
attention heaping praise in return on the visitors 
frank zappa a 1960s counterculture hero no longer all the rage 
at home found himself feted at every turn in prague his zany 
lyrics appeal to the czech love of the absurd 
charles and di drew rave reviews from hungarians accustomed to 
less regal visitors 
we like what we heard that they help ordinary people a great 
deal and go among ordinary people said pal kontra a hospital 
worker in his 50s waiting on a budapest sidewalk to wave to 
princess diana 
its quite a change from the faces weve been accustomed to 
said budapest homemaker juliana szarka 
for 45 years we had to applaud somebody else noted 
pensioner ilona wilnrotter as she cheered the new arrivals 
at the other end of the social scale the easts new leaders are 
making good use of western good will and the revived interest of 
royalty and nobility in their former domains 
prince karl schwarzenberg scion of a family that once owned 
much of bohemia heads a board of foreign advisers appointed by 
havel to help drum up western investment and interest in the 
newlook czechoslovakia 
long barred by the communists for championing human rights in 
the east from his residence in vienna the czechspeaking prince 
now has an office in the prague castle 
otto von hapsburg once crown prince of hungary and fluent in 
its difficult language is venturing into the eastern reaches of 
the empire his family lost after world war i his latest trip was 
last week to the first session of the new democratically elected 
parliament in budapest 
polands new solidarityled government determined to kick the 
communist habit of following economic plans devised by illeducated 
former peasants and workers enlisted sachs a harvard university 
economist to draw up recipes for moving swiftly to a free market 
economy 
dozens of constitutional lawyers and political consultnts have 
made the trip east in recent months advising those unused to 
democracy on everything from drafting new laws to designing catchy 
political ads 
jane fonda one of many stars drawn to havels 
madeforhollywood ascent from political prisoner to president 
perhaps provided the most unusual service to date for the fledgling 
east european democracies 
reportedly fired up by visits to the students who started 
