president bush today assured bolivian 
president jaime paz zamora that you and your countrymen will not 
stand alone in fighting cocaine and trying to improve bolivias 
ailing economy 
winding up three hours of talks at the white house bush 
promised he would seek a substantial increase in economic aid for 
bolivia next year beyond the 88 million earmarked for this year 
he said paz in their private talks had stressed the importance of 
bolivia receiving development assistance 
paz standing alongside bush at a farewell ceremony on the south 
lawn pledged full cooperation in antidrug efforts 
we are fervent allies and we are ready to give you all of our 
efforts and all of our cooperation to everything that would be 
of a common interest paz said 
bush credited paz with overseeing the destruction of more acres 
of coca production in the first four months of the year than was 
eradicated during all of 1989 
saying that bolivia deserves us help bush said you and 
your countrymen will not stand alone in the fight against cocaine 
or in the drive for economic development 
because we do want what you want and that is economic benefit 
for your people bush said and so together were going to wage 
a strong fight 
