americans can now order postage stamps by 
phone all day every day 
the us postal service announced tuesday that it has set up a 
nationwide stampsbyphone system operating 24 hours every day 
customers can buy stamps using major credit cards by calling 
18007826724 1800stamp24 
the agency tested the concept between 1987 and 1989 it has now 
hired the dallasbased firm tmi corp to handle the operation 
the system is expected to be most useful to small businesses 
but can also be important to the elderly the handicapped and 
others for whom a trip to the post office can be difficult or 
timeconsuming 
stamps will be sold at face value plus a 3 service charge per 
order and mailed to the buyer they will be available in sheets of 
50 rolls of 100 or 500 and booklets the service also will sell 
postal cards and stamped envelopes 
