tehran is the worlds most expensive city in 
dollar terms costing nearly twice as much as it does to live in 
new york according to a survey of 83 cities published tuesday 
despite high levels of inflation the continual decline of many 
currencies in latin american countries has ensured they remain 
financially attractive to expatriates quito the capital of 
