government spokesman shaw yuming urged the radio ship to 
observe international laws that ban unauthorized broadcasts 
the government has not and will not become involved in the 
operation of the radio ship shaw said 
shaw made his remarks after top government officials met to 
discuss how to handle the touchy problems raised by the radio ship 
the chinese government has warned that any help provided by 
taiwan for the ship would be considered an open provocation 
the ships presence could jeopardize a recent thaw in the 
historically chilly relations between taipei and the communist 
government in beijing tensions across the 100mile taiwan strait 
have eased marked by increased trade and travel between the two 
countries in recent years 
the ships spokesman xu tianfang said the goddess of democracy 
was scheduled to arrive in the northern taiwanese port of keelung 
on friday to refuel and take on provisions before heading to 
international waters to begin broadcasts 
