<TEXT>
lithuania is cutting meat shipments to soviet 
ministries by 10 percent in hopes of using the scarce food to 
barter with soviet factories for oil and other supplies a 
government spokesman said tuesday 
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev has cut off oil and most 
natural gas shipments to lithuania in an attempt to force it to 
rescind laws backing its march 11 declaration of independence the 
breakaway republic which expects to run out of oil by next week 
already has laid off 12500 people for lack of fuel 
lithuania will sell some of the meat to its own people and use 
the rest for barter trade said aidas palubinskas of the government 
press office 
meat is in extremely short supply in the soviet union making it 
a valuable item for trade to workers in factories that produce 
items lithuania needs 
the soviet government newspaper izvestia promptly accused 
lithuania of cutting milk and meat supplies to strike back against 
the soviet sanctions 
lithuania has decided to retaliate izvestia said it has 
nothing to lose meat shops in vilnius now are selling only cows 
hoofs and pigs heads 
lithuanian president vytautas landsbergis denied that vengeance 
played any part in the decision he cited the soviet failure to 
ship feed grain to the republic 
lithuanias antiblockade committee on tuesday ordered 
preparation of a list of other strategic goods that may be pulled 
from export in the future the press office said 
the soviet union has virtually halted shipments of wood and 
certain plastics since the blockade began last month the press 
office said metal supplies have been cut by half paper shipments 
by 25 percent 
at a news conference tuesday evening landsbergis also advised 
lithuanians not to be bothered by soviet soldiers marching through 
