pleaded guilty tuesday to five counts of political corruption 
moore 67 faces up to 36 years in prison and 12 million in 
fines he was released on a 10000 personal recognizance bond 
pending his scheduled sentencing july 10 
us attorney michael carey said the government will make no 
sentencing recommendation as part of its agreement with moore 
the former governor agreed april 12 to plead guilty to the 
indictment accusing him of crimes involving his 1984 campaign and 
his 198589 term moore also served as governor in 19691977 
as other west virginians went to the polls in the states 
