plans western european nations have been an important source of 
aid and support for the anc and de klerk hopes they will help to 
control more radical black elements that oppose any peaceful 
solution with the white government 
de klerk said he was visiting european leaders to tell them that 
instead of pressure south africa needs encouragement 
this does not mean interference he added 
de klerk is accompanied by foreign minister pik botha and other 
officials 
we have such a good case to present at the moment that im not 
worried about the outcome of the tour he said 
