us district judge edward rafeedie urged the panelists to 
search your hearts and minds before asking to be excused from 
the case because of hardship 
the trial focusing on the internationally sensitive 1985 
slaying of the drug enforcement administration agent is expected 
to last about two months 
more than half of the 250 possible jurors said it would cause 
financial or other hardships to be away from their jobs for so 
long but 118 prospects said they could serve and were given a 
37page questionnaire to fill out before actual questioning begins 
in court wednesday 
the questionnaire asked how much jurors had read or heard about 
the highly publicized camarena investigation 
they were asked to disclose whether they had read about 150 
