system nasa said tuesday 
engineers need time to assess the situation said nasa 
administrator richard truly i dont see it to be an 
earthshattering problem 
the launch had been scheduled for may 16 or may 17 
if a valve that doesnt seem to be working properly has to be 
changed nasa would prefer doing that at the launch pad truly 
said the procedure has never been performed there however and 
officials are uncertain how many days that might take 
