the european community signed accords 
tuesday with east germany and bulgaria virtually completing the 
first stage of a bid to boost trade and economic links across a 
oncedivided continent 
the ec already signed trade and economic cooperation pacts with 
the soviet union hungary and poland and on monday it finalized an 
agreement with czechoslovakia 
romania remains the only east european nation changing to 
democracy and free enterprise with which the ec has no such accord 
negotiations to replace a 1980 pact are expected to open soon 
the 10year accords with eastern europe provide for economic 
cooperation in many sectors including farming the environment and 
easing curbs on imports of east european goods 
currently trade between eastern europe and the european 
community totals 50 billion a year half of which involves the 
soviet union 
on april 28 the ec said it was ready to start a second stage of 
economic relations with eastern europe talks for association 
accords that also cover political consultations 
yet some east europeans are eager to become ec members quickly 
czechoslovakia wants to join by 1999 but the ec citing 
dramatic differences in economic development has ruled out full 
membership for the time being for any east european nation 
one exception is east germany which will join after merging 
with west germany 
the 10year eceast german accord on trade and economic 
cooperation signed on tuesday is a formality it will be changed 
once the two germanys create an economic and monetary union and 
will disappear with formal unification 
until then irish foreign minister gerard collins said this 
trade and economic cooperation agreement will help to bring the two 
parties closer together 
collins whose country holds the ecs rotating presidency 
signed the east german and bulgarian accords on behalf of the ec at 
two separate ceremonies economics minister gerhard pohl signed for 
east germany and bulgarian prime minister andrey loukanov signed 
for his country 
pohl said east germany hoped to boost exports of machine tools 
textiles chemicals and electronic products and looked forward to 
foreign investments from the ec nations 
via technology transfer we will be able to get support for our 
industries he said 
the ecbulgaria accord provides for improved market access 
for bulgarian products and commercial cooperation which is an 
important step towards bulgarian membership of the general 
agreement of tariffs and trade collins said 
