william e schiller retired chairman of 
the board of hershey foods corp has died he was 81 
schiller had retired from the company in march 1974 he died may 
2 at hershey medical center from heart disease spokeswoman deborah 
saline said tuesday 
he joined hershey foods in 1947 as a comptroller and the next 
year was named treasurer and elected to the board of directors he 
became vice president and treasurer in 1956 and chairman of the 
board and treasurer in 1965 
he was a certified public accountant in the chicago and new york 
offices of arthur andersen and co for 14 years before joining 
hershey 
he was a director of the hershey trust co milton hershey 
school ms hershey foundation and the hershey bank he was a 
former chairman of the pennsylvania chamber of commerce 
he was born in sydney mines nova scotia and received 
bachelors and masters degrees from the university of michigan 
he is survived by his wife mary two daughters kathryn s 
