companies to provide paid parental leaves voluntarily but he is 
unwilling to force them to do it 
fitzwater defended the adminstrations stance amid criticism 
from the measures sponsor that it is a rebuff to working families 
it would be most unfortunate if my party which so strongly 
supports family values were to turn its back on working families 
women children grandma and grandpa said rep marge roukema 
rnj 
at one point in his daily news briefing fitzwater suggested that 
workers look for other jobs if they or their unions could not 
negotiate parental leave with their employer 
he later backed off that suggestion saying the high priority 
is to make work and family complementary we urge all employers 
to find sensitive and flexible leave policies but the government 
should not dictate it 
these are the kinds of rigidity that cause companies to not be 
able to hire people and cause greater levels of unemployment 
fitzwater said 
its at the point at which it becomes mandatory that we say 
the negative risks outweigh the benefits he said 
white house chief of staff john sununu assured business leaders 
in a private meeting monday that bush would veto the family and 
medical leave bill scheduled for house action wednesday his threat 
was recounted by business lobbyists who attended the session and 
was confirmed by a sununu aide who asked not to be identified by 
name 
the bill has bipartisan support but is opposed by business 
groups it requires employers with 50 or more workers to offer 
unpaid time off with job and benefit protection for the care of 
newborn newly adopted or seriously ill children as well as to 
deal with personal health problems or ill spouses or parents 
